Thursday is International Nurses Day. On this day, nurses are honoured for their work and dedication, especially over the last two years of the Covid-19 pandemic. Gift of the Givers is honouring those who give back to the sick. eNCA reporter Nobesuthu Hejana is on that story. Courtesy of #DStv403 PAARL - More than 300 nurses from the Paarl Provincial Hospital were honoured on International Nurses’ Day. Gift of the Givers says health workers have been the backbone of the country for the two and half years during the Covid-19 pandemic. Many of the nurses have lost loved ones or colleagues to the virus and on Thursday they were honoured for their contribution. READ: Nurses call for COVID-19 relief workers to be hired Paarl Provincial CEO Francois Van Der Watt said: “Just thank you for your sacrifice, thank you for being willing to pitch up when others could stay home. We really appreciate the sacrifices you’ve made, we salute your bravery and we celebrate your kindness.” The Paarl Provincial Hospital management says it lost two staff members from the virus, * eNCA’s Nobesuthu Hejana reports.